---
description: Two-agent filesystem collaboration protocol
alwaysApply: true
---

If the user asks to initialize, prepare, or configure a new run or asks for the
two launch prompts, follow the `swarm-init` rule instead of entering the run.

Otherwise, when `.swarm/` exists, the user assigns you agent-a or agent-b, or
unread mail exists in `.swarm/mailbox`, read `.swarm/PROTOCOL.md` completely
before task work. Then read `.swarm/ROSTER.md`, `.swarm/MODE`, and
`.swarm/TASK.md`. Never guess your agent id; ask if it was not assigned.
